<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00044</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTIONALIZING A TEN PERCENT BUDGETARY ALLOCATION OF BARANGAYS FOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF PROGRAMS, PROJECTS, ACTIVITIES, AND SERVICES FOR SENIOR CITIZENS, AMENDING FOR THIS PURPOSE THE PERTINENT PROVISIONS OF REPUBLIC ACT 7160 OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "LOCAL GOVERNMENT CODE" AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Authorizes the allocation of ten percent (10%) of the total internal revenue allotment (IRA) for barangays for the implementation of their plans, programs, projects, activities, and services for senior citizens.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>QUIMBO, ROMERO &quot;MIRO&quot; S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Gonzales (A.P.) (006 2016-08-03)</td><td>2. Zamora (M.C.) (011 2016-08-16)</td><tr><td>3. Floirendo (015 2016-08-24)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LOCAL GOVERNMENT ON 2016-07-26</td></tr></table>